messages.message: @Serena I checked but did not find anything in the logs which would indicate why it would return “”.
Can we make some sort of ticket to track looking into this? I know we already have the bug ticket but will be important to get to the bottom of this behaviour
Do we have reproducible steps? Not sure who is investigating this but I’d suggest enabling debug logs in model-service and app-tasks for started to look for clues for the missing values.

i applied `log_level: DEBUG` to both `model-service` and `celery-app-tasks`

currently waiting for `model-service` and `celery-app-tasks` to restart in this environment

after these services re-deploy, @Sankeerthana / @Shridhar Kawalkar can you trigger another app run?

@Hamish i've created a bug ticket to track

for now, i've assigned this to Jordy since the issue is with the response returned by `ibllm` when running fields in an app run (see the `value: ""` or `value: "N/A"` in `__model_result` in this screenshot (https://instabase.slack.com/files/U01CZ3LBFU4/F08V5TUMEN8/screenshot_2025-06-02_at_11.10.46___pm.png))

FYI I'm not too concerned about the issue from a personal POC point of view. Its more this behaviour in general and how it affects customers developing on AI Hub - we need to make sure we get it right :blush:
